commit 5f5999aaf73c61243c3e12a8aa3a52095b26b965
Author: Sean Thornton <sthornton8@outlook.com>
Date:   Sat Jun 20 22:55:25 2026 +0000

    Fix: 'ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE cannot affect row a second time' on apply
    
    The Wahapedia export apparently contains at least one duplicate row
    for the same conflict key (datasheet_id+line, or id) in one of the
    upserted tables. Postgres rejects an entire upsert batch outright
    if it contains two rows with the same key -- this surfaced as a 500
    on /api/admin/import/apply.
    
    Added dedupeByKey(), run before every upsertInBatches() call. Keeps
    the LAST occurrence of each duplicate key (the later row in file
    order is the more likely current value if Wahapedia's export lists
    the same key twice with different data) and logs a warning naming
    the table, the conflict key, and the specific duplicated key
    values, so this stays visible rather than being silently papered
    over.
    
    Verified against a fake Supabase client that reproduces Postgres's
    actual rejection behavior (throws the same '21000' error if a batch
    contains a duplicate key): confirmed applyImport throws without the
    fix and succeeds with it, and confirmed the normal no-duplicates
    case is unaffected (same row counts, no warning logged).

